---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Circular Saw Blades | Industrial Carbide & HSS Blades"
  description="High-performance circular saw blades for industrial applications. Carbide-tipped, HSS, and cermet blades. Custom tooth configurations available."
>
  <section class="gradient-hero text-white py-20">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold mb-6">Circular Saw Blades</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-blue-100">
          Industrial-grade circular blades from 10" to 84" diameter. Carbide-tipped, HSS, and specialty grades.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="prose-custom">
        <h2>Industrial Circular Saw Blade Solutions</h2>
        <p>
          Circular saw blades are the backbone of sawmill operations and metal fabrication facilities. 
          We provide precision-engineered blades designed to meet the rigorous demands of large-scale production.
        </p>

        <h3>Blade Specifications</h3>
        <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl my-8">
          <table class="w-full">
            <thead>
              <tr class="border-b-2 border-gray-200">
                <th class="text-left py-3 font-semibold text-primary">Specification</th>
                <th class="text-left py-3 font-semibold text-primary">Range</th>
                <th class="text-left py-3 font-semibold text-primary">Notes</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="text-gray-700">
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-200">
                <td class="py-3 font-medium">Diameter</td>
                <td class="py-3">10" - 84"+</td>
                <td class="py-3">Larger sizes available</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-200">
                <td class="py-3 font-medium">Kerf (Thickness)</td>
                <td class="py-3">0.125" - 0.375"</td>
                <td class="py-3">Standard industrial range</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-200">
                <td class="py-3 font-medium">Arbor Size</td>
                <td class="py-3">1" - 2.5"</td>
                <td class="py-3">Custom sizes available</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="py-3 font-medium">Tooth Count</td>
                <td class="py-3">24 - 120+</td>
                <td class="py-3">Application-specific</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <h3>Tooth Configurations</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Flat Top (FT):</strong> Ripping operations, straight cuts along grain</li>
          <li><strong>Alternate Top Bevel (ATB):</strong> Smooth crosscuts, clean finishes</li>
          <li><strong>Triple Chip Grind (TCG):</strong> Hard materials, laminates, non-ferrous metals</li>
          <li><strong>High ATB:</strong> Fine crosscutting, melamine, veneer</li>
          <li><strong>Combination:</strong> Mixed tooth patterns for versatility</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Carbide Grade Selection</h3>
        <p>Choose the right carbide grade for your application:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>C-2:</strong> General purpose, balance of hardness and toughness</li>
          <li><strong>C-3:</strong> Abrasive materials, particleboard, MDF</li>
          <li><strong>C-4:</strong> Non-ferrous metals, high-silica woods</li>
          <li><strong>C-1:</strong> Maximum hardness for specialized applications</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Blade Types by Application</h3>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 my-8">
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mb-2">Rip Blades</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">24-40 teeth. Fast, aggressive cuts along the grain for dimensional lumber.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mb-2">Crosscut Blades</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">60-80 teeth. Smooth cuts across grain, precision finishing work.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mb-2">Combination</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Mixed tooth configurations for shops needing versatility.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h3>Operating Parameters</h3>
        <p>
          Proper blade speed (RPM) is critical for performance and longevity. Typical ranges:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Large sawmill blades: 3,000 - 6,000 RPM</li>
          <li>Medium industrial: 4,000 - 8,000 RPM</li>
          <li>Metal cutting: 1,000 - 3,000 RPM (material dependent)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-gray-50 py-16">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-primary mb-4">Need Circular Saw Blades?</h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-8">
        We stock and service all major brands. Custom manufacturing available.
      </p>
      <a href="/contact" class="bg-secondary text-white font-bold px-8 py-4 rounded-lg hover:bg-primary transition">
        Get a Quote
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
